The paper discusses artificial neural networks and computational neuroscience models, which are typically studied in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The focus on efficiency and adaptivity in neuromorphic processing devices suggests a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of embodied agents that interact with the environment suggests a connection to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The discussion of learning and adaptation suggests a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the use of mixed-signal analog/digital circuits suggests a connection to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
